Listing Title: Fully furnished 4bd/2bath/2car Hous
Description:
The home is very clean, fully upgraded with contemporary furniture, hardwood floors, new carpet in all rooms, and granite countertops in kitchen. It is Ideal for a family holiday, relocating professional or someone seeking a temporary home while work

4 Bed, 2 Bath fully furnished corporate house in a clean and quiet Arlington residential community and comfortably sleeps up to 10 people.

Features 
• High speed internet access 
• Washer/dryer in Unit, 
• Side by side Fridge/freezer 
• Dishwasher/built in microwave. 
• Furnished - with 3 Queen Beds and Beddings. 
• Utilities/Basic Cable/Internet included 
• Maid service - (optional and available upon request for a fee)

Easy access to the home. I provide an access code after payment and before check-in date.

Quiet Neighborhood

Close hwy 360/I-20/Arlington to Park Mall, Cowboy Stadium, Rangers ballpark stadium within 10 to 20 mins - 35mins to downtown dallas. 

Neighborhood: •5 mins from new upscale Arlington Highlands mall 
• 5 -- 7 Mins from LA Fitness club 
•Close to Walgreens, Krogers, Shops & a Variety of Restaurants. 
• Also 20 -23 mins from DFW Airport (35 -40 mins from Love field Airport). 
• Unit is located approximately 15 -- 20mins to Downtown Fort Worth

Parking is available at the home. You can rent vehicles at the DFW, Love Field and Arlington airports.

I will provide details of access to the home about a week before Check-in date.

Listing Title: Unit 2 Cowboy Stadium Homes ,LLC Corporate rentals
Description:
Nice, comfortable 3 bdrm/2ba home that sleeps 7 with shared beds or 4 with single beds. Central to the DFW Metroplex. This home has easy access to N/S highway 360 and E/W Interstate 30. If accommodating more guests, there are twin mattresses available to be placed on the floor for temporary stay. This home has a tankless waterheater, so no cold showers for anyone and no waiting.  High speed internet and w/d make this a corporate dream.

***Rent this wonderful three bedroom, two bathroom house with all the comforts of home.  In the middle of the entertainment district of Arlington, it sits  ONE BLOCK from ATT Stadium.  It is 1 mile from Rangers ball park and 1 mile from Six Flags and Hurricane Harbor.  Dead center in the DFW Metroplex you will have easy access to Interstate 30 (E or W bound) or hwy 360 (N & S bound).  Set in a quiet neighborhood you are close to shopping and restaurants with an easy walk to the locations.  
The home sleeps 8-10 people, configured as :  King (2) Queen (2) + twin (1),  Full (2),  Twin Roll away (1)---(& for additional people two chairs that fold into beds on floor. (2)---***if you don't mind roughing it.  There are plenty of additional pillows, linens and blankets available for a comfortable night's sleep. The Kitchen has a gas stove, microwave, toaster, Keurig and regular coffee pot.  There is also a blender and mixer, with ample pots and pans, silverware and additional amenities.** Please note, there is not a dishwasher in the kitchen.  You are required to wash your own dishes.  Soap and sponges/washcloths and brushes are provided.  The backyard is made for relaxing under a huge oak tree in which you have a view of the awesome ATT Stadium right in front of you.  IT'S AWESOME AT NIGHT!!!  Very Majestic!!! The long driveway lends itself to security of your vehicle as it is close to the house and away from the street.  The driveway can accommodate up to 4 vehicles. (accounting for stacking of cars behind one another)

Listing Title: Cowboy Stadium Homes ,LLC Corporate rental Unit 3
Description:
Warmly decorated and spacious makes this home a must stay!!The central location to D/FW makes your stay convenient and easy on the budget. Easy access to N/S highway 360 and E/W Interstate 30.  Lots of amenities provided. Two TVs, one in Living area and one in Queen bedroom with Direct TV!  The third bedroom has bathroom attached and is right off the kitchen area.

The whole house is accessible to guests.  Bedrooms are light, but have room darkening curtains for sleeping in!!  Front porch is comfortable for sitting and enjoying the evening. Large backyard deck for tailgating or enjoying your morning cup of coffee.   Walk through the backyard gate and across the street and you are at the Stadium in less than 5 minutes!!  Walk to all the shopping and entertainment areas easily!

You will be renting the whole house and have access to all areas.  All rooms are spacious and comfortably furnished.  Attention to details is what this owner is proud of.  Small things like a first aid kit, sewing kit and flashlights in the event of lost power during a storm.....All the comforts of home with lots of dishes, pots and pans...and even coffee and the fixins are provided.

The host of this home is always available for any needs or communication. Please give a voice call, not a text if you need host after 10:00 pm or if there is an emergency.  Access for self check in through coded lock box on front door, and additional lock box with key.  Codes given ahead of time by host when contact is made prior to check in.

This is a residential neighborhood, most homes built in the 1940s.  Mostly families and retirees.  It is a bit lower income, but safe and relatively quiet with the exception of stadium event. You are only blocks away from all the excitement.

Listing Title: Unit 1 Cowboy Stadium Homes,LLC  Corporate rentals
Description:
This 1940's home holds nostalgia and charm.It has been updated and remodeled.It is clean, comfortable and safe. It has a great sitting area on the deck and a large backyard.It is close to family friendly activities, restaurants, dining, and nightlife.You’ll love it because of the comfy beds, the kitchen, washer & dryer and spaciousness. A good place for business travelers & families. I provide A LOT of amenities. Bdrms have room darkening shades for sleeping in.

There are two coffee makers, a drip style and a Keurig.  Full size washer and dryer available. Lots of Amenities provided(review below under "Other things to note") Separate back bedroom and bathroom allow for privacy with an entrance from the parking space.  You can also access it through a backyard door as not to have to go through the middle bedroom.  There is a large, shaded deck out back for visiting or just relaxing. Two parking spots in back and more along the curb up front.The bedrooms are spacious as is the layout of the house.

The whole house is accessible by all guests. PARKING:  CITY OF ARLINGTON ORDINANCE DOES NOT ALLOW ANY STREET PARKING DURING SPECIAL EVENTS AT THE STADIUM.  THERE IS ENOUGH ROOM FOR 2 CARS IN THE PARKING AREA BEHIND THIS HOME.  ON NON-EVENT DAYS THERE IS ROOM FOR TWO MORE CARS PARKED ALONG THE CURB IN FRONT OF THE HOUSE. TOWING IS ENFORCED AND TICKETING WILL OCCUR IF YOU PARK ON ANY GRASSY AREAS.

I am available 24/7 during your stay via call or text. (If you need me after 10:00 pm, please give a VOICE CALL)In the event of emergencies there is a House Book with helpful information.
  Review under the "Booking tab"--additional rules listed below HOUSE RULES.  (scroll down)

You are in the heart of the Entertainment District.  Safest areas are along Collins street-East and North of the house.  This house is equipped with an in house safe and mock security cameras around the perimeter. This is an older neighborhood, homes built in the 1940s.

PARKING:  CITY OF ARLINGTON ORDINAN

Listing Title: "The Treehouse" apartment
Description:
WINTER DISCOUNTS 
Our 2 bedroom, 1 bath, second floor garage apartment with central air and deck sleeps 4.

The main bedroom has a queen Sleep Number® bed. The 2nd has twin beds. The entire place is light and airy.  Enjoy the full kitchen, laundry and deck space.

This is a low cost solution for a well furnish and artsy space.  Dubbed "The Treehouse" due to its second story location with widows and deck areas up "in the trees".  Exterior lighting accents the home, giving it a comfortable and safe appeal.  The deep swimming pool helps make the Texas outdoors enjoyable especially during the summer.  

As Host, we live in the main home and are usually available should there be any Guest concerns or other needs.

Guest have access to the gated parking, swimming pool (in season), gas grill, and laundry room.

Last minute reservations accepted...we will accommodate if we can.

We will interact with our Guest to the level that they desire.  Guest are living in a separate building with their own deck space. The guest house has its own separate access and parking area.  This provides needed privacy while the outdoor space (shared pool and grill areas) may be used as needed to relax and interact.

This neighborhood is well established, near central Arlington and UTA.  Built in the early 1960, each home is unique and the trees are beautiful (for Texas).

There is easy access (10 min) to the Arlington Entertainment District, Texas Ranger Ballpark and the Dallas Cowboy Stadium.  

We are centrally located between both Dallas and Fort Worth and directly south of DFW Airport; a 30 to 40 minute drive to each of these locations.

The State of Texas Occupancy tax (6%) is shown in quote.  The City of Arlington tax (9% hotel tax) already included in nightly rate that is shown.

Listing Title: The Suite
Description:
‘The Suite' has a large bedroom, 2 bathrooms, sitting room and kitchenette  with central air that sleeps 3.

Bedroom has queen Sleep Number bed and sleeper sofa in sitting room.  Quiet area to relax and the deep swimming pool helps make the Texas outdoors enjoyable - especially during the summer.

'The Suite' was a 'Mother-in-Law' suite that is separate and isolated from the main part of my house, which is a single family home in a quiet, well established neighborhood in Central Arlington.  

'The Suite' includes a bedroom with a queen sleep-number bed; separate living area with sofa, TV and kitchenette with table, small fridge, microwave and coffee station.  There are two bathrooms, each with shower, toilet and sink.

Guest have access to the swimming pool (in season), gas grill, and laundry room.  You can come and go as you please through a separate side entrance along our gated lit driveway with parking on street or in driveway.

I live in the main house and am available to answer questions.  Interaction with Guest will be to the level that they desire. If you're ready for a quiet getaway - privacy is yours.  The outdoor space -pool and grill areas are shared - may be used to relax and interact.

Last minute reservations accepted...we will accommodate if we can.

This neighborhood is well established, near central Arlington and UTA. Built in the early 1960, each home is unique and the trees are beautiful (for Texas)

There is easy access (10 min) to the Arlington Entertainment District including Six Flags, Hurricane Harbor, Globe Life Park (Rangers stadium) and the AT&T (Cowboy) Stadium.  University of Texas at Arlington is also close.

We are centrally located between both Dallas and Fort Worth and directly south of DFW Airport; a 30 to 40 minute drive to each of these locations.

Listing Title: Beautiful home in Arlington

Semi-private pond/fishing

Listing Title: Earthen Cottage on Small Ecovillage
Description:
***30 nights minimum stay***

This hand sculpted dwelling feels like an indigenous hut with comfy country furnishings. 

It is at the back of The Garden of Eden eco-village, a thriving small community dedicated to sustainability and philanthropy! With over 3 acres of land, wildcrafted gardens, and families living here, the vibe is wholesome and progressive. 

Enjoy the privacy of the secluded cottage, or join us on the grounds or in the main house for activities or communal meals by donation.

The Cob cottage is cozy and private, though it is rustic and quite simple. As part of our ecovillage culture, we are dedicated to living sustainably and the Cob cottage is a great showcase for that!

Cob is a mixture of sand, straw, clay, and water - this sweet little cottage is literally handmade out of Earth! It is a very peaceful and oh so unique place to stay :)

The insulating nature of cob is such that it stays a little warmer in winter and a bit cooler in summer. 

Electricity DOES run to the Cob house. It has a space heater in winter and a small AC unit for the summer months.

Wifi does not reach to the cottage in the back of our property, but you can come to the main house to connect.

There is a lock on the door for your privacy and comfort. We ask a  refundable $20 deposit for the key to the lock.

We will provide a reusable water bottle filled with filtered water in your space. You may refill this with filtered water from our kitchen and use for the duration of your stay so you don't have to go to the store and buy bottled water (which is not only poor quality water often no better than tap water, but is also packaged in disposable plastics that harm health and pollute the earth). If you would like to take the sustainable water bottle with you on your journey, they are available in exchange for a small donation.

We provide a complimentary continental breakfast for you with hot tea, seasonal fruits, a variety of organic milks & cereals, organic breads, and deliciou

Listing Title: Comfy Bed only 2 Miles from AT&T, Ballpark & More

In the heart of the metroplex  centrally located between Fort Worth and Dallas. 

Within walking distance to River Legacy Park and 2.5 miles from AT&T Stadium, Globe Life Park, Six Flags Over Texas and Hurricane Harbor. In addition, you can find shopping, restaurants and entertainment at nearby Lincoln Square.

Quiet neighborhood in a very established part of North Arlington.

The house is open and airy with a beautiful and peaceful pond out back (seasonally).  Your bedroom has a queen sized bed, 32 inch TV with Roku and a comfy homey feel.

Private Bedroom,  Bath, Porch,  Semi-Private Living Room, Kitchen and Laundry

This neighborhood is licated 2.5 miles from the Arlington entertainment district (Ballpark, Stadium, Six Flags, Hurricane Harbor) and surrounded by mature trees. Walking distance to River Legacy Park nature center.

If you are working in downtown Fort Worth or Dallas I am within 10 minutes from 2 TRE train stations or a 30 minute drive to both downtown centers.

Listing Title: Cozy townhome near Cowboys Stadium
Description:
This is a two-bedroom townhome in a quiet, safe, working-class community that is only a 15-20 minute drive to AT&T Stadium, and minutes from several shopping centers including the Grand Prairie Premium Outlets.  Less than 10 min from UT Arlington.

This is a great sized townhome for a small family, with fun bunk beds for the kids (or adults!) and a master bedroom with a comfortable memory foam mattress and premium bedding.  Full kitchen, with basic cookingware lets you stay in a home away from home.

Please note there is no TV, but you are welcome to stream shows / videos over the WiFi. 

Also note: As this is a townhome with shared walls, you may hear some sound from the neighbors. If it is an issue during your stay, please let us know so we can address it with the management office.

The entire home is available for guest use, except for the garage and back yard which is off-limits.

The hosts will be available by phone, text and email to help with anything at all!

This is a quiet, safe, and peaceful working-class neighborhood, but is close to:

- AT&T Cowboys Stadium (15-20 min drive)
- Shopping centers like Grand Prairie Premium Outlets and the Arlington Highlands Mall (5-10 min drive)
- Target (5-10 min drive)
- UT Arlington (10-15 min drive)
- Several parks
- DFW Airport (25-30 min drive without traffic)

The community is located about 25 minutes driving from DFW Airport (without traffic), and about 30 minutes to downtown Dallas, or 30 minutes from Fort Worth.  

There is not much public transportation so a car is highly recommended.

There is no covered parking, but guests may park on the street next to the townhome.  

If you should need to take out the trash, there are dumpsters located around the left side of the townhome where the garages are.

Description:

This is a quaint house for a small family/friends of 6 people. It’s a 3 bedroom/2bath home, centrally located in Dallas/Ft. Worth, in the heart of Arlington, Texas. The attention to detail in the decor makes this space very unique. Soft charming furniture pieces and mixed wood, metal, and iron create a very eclectic feel to this space. It is a very safe neighborhood and perfect for all the entertainment nearby (AT&T Stadium, TX Rangers Ballpark, eSports Stadium, Six Flags, Epic Waters Indoor Waterpark, Arlington Convention Center, & 15 -20 minutes to everything located in Dallas & Fort Worth). The home has 2 flat screen tv’s in the master and living room with cable and mobile internet. This is an entire home rental so you will have it to yourself.

You have full access to front & back yard and entire home including laundry room, coffee/wine room, & a driveway that accommodates 2 cars.

I'll be available to help during your stay if you need anything.

Staying at my space you are central to Dallas & Ft. Worth. It’s about a 20 minute drive to downtown in both areas. Arlington is home of the Dallas Cowboys, Texas Rangers, & Six Flags over Texas.

Rental car service is accessible at airport along with Lyft & Uber. The best way to get around the DFW area is through vehicle transportation.

Description:
Warm 2 BD, 2 1/2 Bath Townhome with Garage by Lake Arlington.  15 min. from Rangers, Cowboys and Six Flags.  30 min. from DFW airport, downtown Dallas and Ft. Worth.  Beautiful home with artist's works and designated office space.    This "unique" rental is available for a minimum of a month with month to month renewals.

•Ideal for longer stays, with designated office space and office equipment, high speed (12MBPS) internet, printer. 
•Ideal for families with children who like Cowboys or Rangers game or Six Flags/Hurricane Harbor.   
•Sleeps four comfortably - One Queen Posturpedic bed with separate electronic controls, 1 Twin Bed, 1 Trundle and sleepable space for a fifth person if needed in exercise room. 
•Garage for medium size car
•5 minutes to grocery, office supply store, shopping, fast food, restaurants.
•5 Minutes walk to beautiful Lake Arlington. 
•Upstairs exercise room/Reading room with Stationary Bicycle
•Television has Cable,HBO and HDMI cable for connecting to computer to Stream Netflix, Amazon Prime and other streaming services. 
•Jacuzzi tub in Master Bath. 
•Kitchen with full cooking capabilities 
•Large Patio space with BBQ grill for grilling.

Guests are free to access all areas of the house, including kitchen and garage, except for closets marked "HOST USE ONLY."  Please let us know if there will be more than 3 guests staying with your party.

I am hard of hearing but am local.   My son will help me manage your stay.   This should be considered temporary housing for a minimum of one month stay with indefinite month to month renewal.

Quiet residential neighbourhood on Lake Arlington.  Beautiful for walks, fishing.  Townhome community is small.

Arlington has no public transportation.  However UBER and LYFT can get you just about anywhere (including downtown Ft. Worth or Dallas) for under $25.00.   Download the App today if you don't have it.  Parking is available in the garage and in front of the home.

Description:
The Center of the Entertainment District. Was designed for entertaining multiple guests. It has access to Globe Life Park (lot M) and ATT Stadium, within 5 and 7min walks direct from your back yard! Just up the street are  the restaurants and bars.

This house was designed for open entertaining and easy access for our sports venues and other activities in the metroplex. It's rustic charm and southwestern chic is both modern and inviting. Full cable packages and WiFi access are both provided. A fully equipped kitchen is at your groups disposal. We want our guests to feel the friendly Texas atmosphere during your stay.

Guests have easy access to both stadiums and theme parks in the area.

Host available on request.

Older established quiet neighborhood. It is SURROUNDED by things to do. The new Texas Live development and new ranger stadium (open later next year) as well as ATT, six flags, hurricane harbor, champions park, the Electronic Gaming center and many other things are all within walking distance.

Walking distance from most things in the area. However, Uber, rent bikes,
And even rickshaws/golf carts (on game days) are available in the area.

Access to tickets to the games is possible with advanced inquiries.

2 friendly cats

 No TV in room but have Wifi available.

only about 3 miles from ATTStadium, Ranger Stadium, 6 Flags

Listing Title: 2 Bedroom Condo in Entertainment District
Description:
"Triple Play" condo is a clean, comfortable, well appointed 2 bedroom condo located within minutes to three of DFW's most popular attractions: Cowboys (AT&T) Stadium, Texas Rangers (Globe Life) Ballpark, and Six Flags theme parks.

 - 1.6 miles to AT&T Stadium (Dallas Cowboys)
 - 1.4 miles to Globe Life Ballpark (Texas Rangers)
 - 0.8 miles to Six Flags Hurricane Harbor
 - 2.6 miles to Six Flags Over Texas
 - 11.7 miles to DFW airport
 - 18.6 miles to Dallas
 - 14.8 miles to Fort Worth

Welcoming Texas retreat close to Arlington's entertainment district with all new furnishings, fixtures, and decor.

Room to spread out with two separate bedrooms; both with brand new KING size memory foam mattresses. Plus, sleeper sofa in living room to accommodate extra guests. Sleeps total of 6 guests.

Flat screen TV's in both bedrooms and living room with extended cable package.

Fast, high-speed wireless internet.

Kitchen fully appointed with all new cookware, dishes, basic small appliances, utensils, plus a few extras.

Large bathroom with shared access to master bedroom and hallway.

Private, fenced patio with outdoor seating.

Guests will have access to three community pools, a hot tub, and a fitness center. Washer/Dryer in unit. Kitchen fully stocked.

Available as needed by email, text, or phone.

Great location in a quiet, gated community within walking distance to the entertainment district. Close to DFW international airport; ideal central location between Dallas and Fort Worth with easy access to I-30.

No public transportation nearby, but Uber is prevalent in the area.

Listing Title: Private Entrance!  Close to everything.
Description:
•Private guest suite
•No shared areas 
•Private entrance 
•Semi-private patio 
•Individual A/C & heat 
•Fridge/microwave 
•Netflix/Amazon Prime (Firestick)
•Quiet neighborhood next to City park 
 •Meets COVID cleaning protocols except for the 3-day wait between guests. 
Conveniently located:
Arlington Hosp District – 3 miles, 
Stadium/Entertainment District - 6 miles, UTA - 2 miles, Downtown - 3 miles
•Permit # 20 - 001995 - STR.
Arlington now has mass transit! Check out Via on the App Store.

Better than a high-priced hotel!  You'll enjoy complete privacy, high-thread-count sheets, plush towels, a great mini-bar, individual A/C and space heater, and a CDC-recommended in-room HEPA air purifier which also minimizes allergy symptoms. Extra clean with sanitizing touches.

Your suite is completely  separate from the rest of the townhouse.  You'll have a private entrance from the front patio through the beautiful French doors.  No shared spaces.  
     The suite connects to the main house through the kitchenette.  The door remains closed and locked; there is even a chain to ensure your privacy.  Keeping the bedroom door closed will keep any noise from the main house from disturbing your stay.  I'm a pretty quiet person and am normally upstairs before 11:00.
     While I enjoy meeting my guests, in these days of social distancing, I am listening to the wisdom of the CDC and respecting the need for each of us to limit our contact with others.  Of course,  I can turn down the air, turn up the heat, turn on the light if it's dark, and let you know as soon as the room is clean and ready so you'll have access to the suite as early as possible.  I'll still be here to make sure you're as comfortable as possible.

I am currently working from home, and following social distancing guidelines. If you should need assistance, please reach out to me.

Listing Title: Main St  1 m AT&T Sta 7 Queen + 2 Twins+breakfast
Description:
Our place is centrally located - 1 mile to AT&T Stadium, adjacent to Six Flags, Water & Amusement Parks,  Globe Life baseball Park,  arts & museum, Downtown and the University of Texas in Arlington.  When tired, it is easy to come back to the house to take a shower, enjoy a good meal, and rest on a comfy bed. Our place is right for singles,  couples, families. Air mattresses are available.  The City of Arlington charges 9% Hotel Occupancy Tax billed separate.

The house has 4 bedrooms, 7 Queen beds, and 2 Twins,  and 3 full bathrooms, water heaters, and two A/C-heater units. Plenty of parking the front, back and side driveway.  Has a front porch as well as a lanai.

Use of the entire home.

I'm just a few miles away if you need anything. The house has been completely renovated and is wonderful.

There is an additional "management fee" of 9%. The is the City of Arlington HOT, Hotel Occupancy Tax.  Airbnb collects the State of Texas tax of 6% and pays the State of Texas but not collect The City of Arlington tax of 9%. 

Currently, Airbnb doesn't offer a way to differentiate the charges, so we have to collect and pay the City of Arlington directly.

You are close to downtown Arlington, quiet area plenty of parking

Use Uber and save all the parking fees.

Listing Title: GREAT LOCATION IN DALLAS/FT WORTH AREA - Long term
Description:
My place is close to AT&T Stadium, The Ballpark at Arlington, Hurricane Harbor, Six Flags Over Texas, and dining. Situated between Dallas and Ft Worth so you can quickly get to those cities.  This second floor unit is in a safe, quiet, gated community.  Good for couples, business travelers, and families.  Perfect location if you're moving to the metroplex and need a place or a business traveler. LONG TERM STAY!

This condo is recently remodeled and is very clean and organized.  It has a fully stocked kitchen and bathroom (including towels).  It is set up like a hotel suite so it's very well organized and comfortable for your stay.  There are 2 assigned parking spots.

There is a key pad at the front door and the outside front door is monitored.

I like to give my guests privacy but I'm available to answer questions.

This is a great community!  Very quiet and clean.  People know each other and look out for each other in the complex.  It's a gated complex so it's very safe!.  There is a beautiful pool/spa area and tennis courts.  The location is ideal for staying in the city.  All the main attractions in town are only minutes away.

If you don't have a car, Uber is available in the city.  Lots of places are within walking distance.  There is a grocery store, restaurants, amusement parks... all within walking distance.

Wifi/ Cable will not be included in along term stay over 30 days.

Listing Title: Comfy Garage Apt + Pool Close to FUN!
Description:
Our place is five to seven minutes directly north of AT&T Stadium, and just as close to The Ballpark in Arlington, Six Flags, Hurricane Harbor, restaurants  family-friendly activities, and nightlife. You’ll love our place because of the treed neighborhood near parks and trails, the comfy bed, and the outdoors space. Our place is good for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers. WIFI. DIRECTV.

Be sure to check out our on-line guidebook (also in the apartment) with wonderful local info!

We have a detached garage behind our home, and the Airbnb space is in the apartment above our garage. We think it's a cool set-up that allows you as much privacy as you'd like!

We make check in and check out super easy! We'll send you details before you're set to arrive. It is very streamlined and convenient. We want you to feel as if you are coming and going from your own home.

Guests are welcome to use our pool! We ask there be no running, no swimming alone, and that noise be kept to a minimum out of respect for our neighbors. IF we've agreed to allow a child as a guest, the child must never be alone in the garage apartment or in the backyard. The hot tub does not heat.

Simply text or call me if you need anything. We want you to be comfortable and to have everything you need! We're happy to help.

We've had prospective guests ask if there is a shower. YES, there is a shower, shown on the right in the picture of the bathroom.
The kitchen does not have a built-in oven. It DOES have a convection oven/toaster, microwave, mini-fridge, and coffee pot.

Listing Title: 3 block walk distance-Cowboys & Rangers Stadium!
Description:
The house is 3 easy walking blocks to the AT&T Cowboys Stadium, and a short walk to the Texas Rangers Globe Life Park,  less than a mile drive to Six Flags and Hurricane Harbor! There are shopping malls, strip & outlet malls, & any type of restaurant & bar you could want within 15 mins. There is a short walk to Walmart, Walgreens, and Lincoln Square shopping & dining center. You are 20 min. from downtown Dallas to the east, and 20 min. from downtown Ft.Worth.

Why stay in a hotel when you can relax in an entire house?  Comfortable and cozy, it’s your home away from home! As a guest you will have access to the entire house – a 3 Bedroom, 1 Bath, newly remodeled in 2016, and fully furnished with central heat and air conditioning. The home has nice furniture and décor, new flooring, bathroom and kitchen remodeled, everything is new throughout! 

There are two TV's with Direct TV Satellite and Internet. Ceiling fans in all bedrooms and the living room, and the list goes on and on. The kitchen has everything you need for cooking and baking, refrigerator/freezer with ice maker and water dispenser, and a dishwasher. Full size washer and dryer. All bedroom linens are provided and are high quality and there is plenty of closet space. 
The front bedroom has a pillow-top queen size bed, a twin bed, TV, and closet.  The second bedroom has a pillow-top King size bed with closet. The third bedroom has two queen size pillow top beds. The living room has a sofa that can sleep a smaller person very comfortably. All linen, bedding, and mattresses are new and very clean. The house sleeps 8 comfortably. 

The large private fenced-in backyard has a grill, new patio and table and chairs. There is ample driveway parking for up to 3 cars.

The house rents on average monthly from $2100 to $3000. Please contact me and I will happily work with you on monthly rentals. Please contact me with an inquiry if pricing seems off. Absolutely no parties allowed.

Listing Title: Walk to AT&T Stadium, Ballpark and Texas Live!
Description:
CLEAN HOME. All surfaces professionally sanitized between guests. 
 Our home is in the center of it all! We are walking distance to the Rangers Ballpark and AT&T Stadium. We are in the center of the Metroplex and are a short drive away from so many attractions! Our cozy, fully updated home is family friendly.   There are three bedrooms, two full bathrooms, living, kitchen, dining and a backyard. We have lots of extras like cooking supplies, games, coffee, toiletries, laundry facilities and more!

PERMIT NUMBER: 19-152192-STR 

LOCATION:
The home is situated in an established neighborhood that is next to AT&T Stadium and Globe Life Park, walking distance to many bars, restaurants, Texas Live Entertainment Venue and very close to Interstate 30 & HWY 360.  

It is a:
- 15 minute WALK to AT&T Stadium and Globe Life Park (or 3 minute drive)
- 5 minute drive to Six Flags & Hurricane Harbor
- 5-10 minute walk to Shopping, Restaurants & Bars
- 5 minute drive to Arlington Convention Center or 20 minute walk
- 12 minute drive from Verizon Theatre
- 15 min drive from Epic Waterpark (one of the largest indoor waterparks in the world, perfect for cold and rainy days!)
- 20 minute drive to Downtown Fort Worth & Magnolia Avenue
- 20 minute drive to DFW Airport
- 25 minute drive to Downtown Dallas, Museums, the Art District & Fair Park
- 25 minute drive to the Fort Worth Stockyards & Cattle Drive
- 30 minute drive from Downtown Grapevine, Wineries, Gaylord Texan

SLEEPING SITUATION:
We have two bedrooms that each have a queen bed. 
One bedroom has a queen and two bunk beds (TOP BUNK HAS 125 LB WEIGHT LIMIT)
The Living Room has a couch and air mattress that can be used. We also have a Pack n Play available.

HOUSE:

Listing Title: Fully Furnished Corporate Rental
Description:
We have a cozy one bedroom one bathroom condo that is located in North Arlington. We are walking distance to Hurricane Harbor Water Park or a 3 minute drive. We are also a 7 minute drive to the AT&T stadium, Six Flags over Texas, and the Texas Rangers Ball Park. We are a 25 minute drive to Downtown Dallas and 13 minutes to the Verizon theater. This condo has a strict HOA so we only rent this place out 30 days at a time. It is perfect for traveling nurses and other business travelers. $1600/mo

We have 2 comfortable leather couches with 4 recliner seats. The living room consists of several board games for guests and an additional TV with cable, netflix, HULU, etc.  The master bedroom consists of a TV, full closet, and queen sized bed. There is Wi-Fi throughout the entire condo so you will have an internet connection for tablets, phones, etc. We also have a quiet patio area for your enjoyment.

You will have access to a full kitchen, washer, dryer, and bathroom. You will have detergent pods and dryer sheets for the washer and dryer. There is also a keurig with different flavors of coffee in the kitchen area.  The condo also has a pool and hot tub on site.

We will be available to reach via phone anytime during your visit. We will be about 30 minutes from the premises just in case we are needed at the property.

We are in a really quiet older community. The neighbors are really friendly and will look after your place while you are gone. Most of them are retired and are home most of the day.

There isn't much public transportation but an Uber is always 5 minutes out.

We ask that you do not smoke or bring pets. We do a one time supply of toiletries, towels, sheets, laundry supplies, and dish washing supplies. All of these items will be available at check in. We charge $1600/mo and this includes parking and all utilities.

Description:
My place is close to AT&T Stadium and The Texas Rangers Ball Park, DFW airport, family-friendly activities, and plenty of night life. You’ll love this home because of its character and location. It is centrally located in Arlington with only a 20 minute drive to almost anywhere in the DFW metroplex. You'll also love the neighborhood, comfy beds, the kitchen, and the coziness. Listing Title: Spacious 4BD/3BA. AT&T Stadium is 3.1 mi.Away!!!
Description:
This fully furnished home is very modern and very welcoming. Having two separate living and dining rooms, the house is great for families and large groups. Centrally located only  3.1 miles from AT&T stadium, 4.0 miles from Rangers Stadium, and 4.8 miles from  Six Flags in Arlington. Just minutes from I30 and 360 and close to major shopping and restaurants. Equipped with wifi, cable, and full kitchen this will be your home away from home.

Master bedroom is very spacious and has a King size bed along with walk in closet and spacious remodeled bathroom. Guest bedroom with nautical theme furnished with a queen sized bed, and the guest bedroom down the hall equipped with two twin sized beds. The back private bedroom is equipped with a queen sized bed and office area as well as your private bathroom. Garage with space to park 2 compact cars.

I am happy to check you in and answer any questions that you may have about the property and the area surrounding it.

Neighborhood is very safe and quiet. Just .5 of a mile from the nearest park (Gibbons Park) as well as the Ditto Golf Course.

Uber is allowed in Arlington and recommended if you are limited on cars. If you are going to any sporting events like the Cowboys game allow ample time because even being so close to the stadium it will take you or an Uber driver a while to get through game day traffic and parking.Also, remember that Uber drivers will be over loaded with people after the game so expect to wait for about 30 minutes until one arrives to pick you up. J Gilligan' s is a good alternative to go eat and or dink and pay for a shuttle ($8 per person ) to the game.

Please note that we have designed a key-less access for this property. Now you can be worry free. This place is a must see and stay. It is Central to FT Worth or Dallas and close to the DFW airport.

There are trolley/bus lines available. Six Flags/Hurricane Harbor is approximately 1 mile away. This property has a very easy access to East/West highway, or North/South highway. Arlington Visitors center is right next to the Globe Ballpark and has loads of helpful information.

I welcome all guests from all walks of life, regardless of race, nationalities, cultures, sexuality (LGBTQ), gender, marital status, spiritual preference, pole dancers & anything else I have missed here.

This is a very clean townhouse with 2 1/2 baths. Queen size bed with share bath is a shower/tub combo. Kitchen & Living are common areas. There is a washer/dryer you are welcome to use. Only registered guests are allowed in the house.

Listing Title: Updated, Comfy Home in Entertainment District
Description:
This home has been recently remodeled and stocked with top-of-the-line mattresses, sheets, towels, etc. Fully stocked kitchen. Convenient location -  about 1/2 mile from ATT (Cowboys) Stadium, Globe Life (Rangers) Stadium, Arlington Convention Center, and about a mile from Six Flags & Hurricane Harbor; 20 minutes to DFW and 25 minutes to both Dallas and Ft Worth. Within walking distance of shopping and  restaurants.

-Luxury pillow top mattresses and linens in all bedrooms
-all three bedrooms have king beds
-the sofa bed is a queen--not as comfy as the others, but we have a down mattress topper for it
-one bath has a tub/shower combo; the other has a shower
-Fully stocked kitchen w/gas stove, oven, microwave, coffee maker (+coffee), tea kettle (+tea), toaster, blender, mixer, fridge/freezer, pots/pans, serving ware, etc. 
-May consider pets in special circumstances
-Nice, big back yard.
-We have a Graco Pack and Play bassinet/play pen. Our grandchildren have slept in it.

Full house, garage, fenced-in backyard, BBQ grill, screened-in porch, plenty of parking.

We are available by phone and have family in the area.

This is a quiet residential neighborhood from our experience. Sometimes you can hear concerts and crowd noises from the front yard (we are close to Cowboys Stadium), but we haven't heard anything from inside.

You can walk to Cowboys Stadium and tons of restaurants and shopping. It's a short drive (one mile) to many attractions such as the Rangers, Six Flags, Hurricane Harbor and more. And about 20 minutes by car to Dallas and Fort Worth. If you're not renting a car, Uber and Lyft are good options.

Listing Title: 2 Bedroom/ SweetTEXAS home!
Description:
The property is close to AT&T Stadium, Six Flags, Globe Life Park (Texas Rangers Stadium) Hurricane Harbor, The Parks Mall, Arlington Highlands, Ripley's Believe it or Not, Verizon Theater at Grand Prairie, TCC (Tarrant Community College) DFW Airport and much more! All of these places are located approximately 20-25 minutes away.  You will love this home because of the coziness and it's centrally located in the Dallas Forth Worth area.

This home is fully furnished with comfy beds. We will provide a custom access code for this property. Great for couples, solo adventures, business travelers, families (with kids) or a group of friends. It will make you feel at home while away from home. Everyone is welcome!

The house is fully furnished: washer, dryer, microwave, oven, fridge, guest bathroom, living room, dining room, kitchen, Wifi and propane grill is available with plenty of backyard! I dont have cable but it is a smart TV where you can connect to Netflix or anything through an HDMI connection. The garage will not be available but you will have available parking on the driveway. Also if you feel like going on an early morning bike ride, I will have two bicycles available for use! You could ride around the neighborhood or just the corners stores that are a mile and half away.

Joe Pool Lake is also located a couple miles away from this location. They have a great seafood Resturant call The Oasis!

I will be off the property during your stay unless you need me for anything. It will be my pleasure to come by and assist.

Neighborhood: It is quiet and peaceful.
Sometimes during the day there are small children playing out on the street. *Please watch out for kids playing.

South Arlington charming & comfortable 3BR/2B house. 8.5 miles from AT&T Stadium, 6 miles from UT Arlington.  This  has recently been remodeled, wood and ceramic tile flooring, and a large master suite. No Carpet! Spacious bedrooms, fully equipped kitchen, washer and dryer. Please carry your personal hygiene protection during the trip to maintain healthy sanitation practices. Be sure to wash your hands often and we wish you a safe and pleasant stay!

We also provide our guests with a Reverse Osmosis Water Filtration System for clean drinking water(So you don't need to buy bottle water)  . Our kitchen is fully equipped. Our laundry room is provided with laundry detergent, fabric softener, and a new washer and dryer. Prior to your arrival, please text me so I can disarm the alarm system remotely. Walmart and Albertson's supermarkets are 1-3 minutes away. AT&T Stadium, 6 miles from UT Arlington. Listing Title: My Texas Oasis
Description:
Lovely 4 bedroom home that is close to ALL the action in the Arlington and Dallas and Fort Worth area.  Custom workout area, outdoor grill area and several areas to "hang-out"... might be the perfect home for your vacation or business trip!

A very open floorplan that allows an easy flow within the home... privacy upstairs with both a separate work-out area, one full bathroom and three very well appointed bedrooms ( 2 with desks). Pleas note that the bunk beds in the 4th bedroom have a maximum weight for each bed of 160 lbs... definitely for children and lighter adults.

They have full access to the house (except garage and attic areas).

Typically, I'm only a text or phone call away... let me know if there is a problem.

The best thing about the neighborhood is that the promixity to EVERYTHING, but it has the feel and warmth of a suburban life style... very secure with a surround wall around the "entire" neighborhood.

Arlington just incorporated a $3 ride share program (similiar to Uber)... the servie will take you anywhere in Arlington proper within the city limits... the Application on your phone is "Via"...

Wifi is available... see other sections of the information.
Also there are assorted board and Card games available... a fun family night for sure!

Perfect for business traveler or couple on the road! Our spacious pool home offers relaxation and a centralized location. We are less than 20 mins from DFW airport, and are within 10 mins drive (less than $12 uberX [4 people]; or less than $20 uberXL [6 people]) to Dallas Cowboys stadium, Texas Rangers stadium, Six Flags Over Texas, Hurricane Harbor and the Arlington Entertainment District. The areas you will NOT have access to are the Master Bedroom, the Garage, my Office, and the Upstairs areas.
The hot tub can be set up for your use with 30-45 min prior request.

I'm happy to chat or hang out with guests as much or as little as you like, and if you have any questions, don't hesitate to pop by the office to ask.

We live on a quiet residential street with free parking for multiple vehicles available on the street. Please park at least 10 feet from the mailbox and recycling bins put out for collection, and do not block any driveways. This is a nice and quiet neighborhood, but I will always recommend against leaving items visible in your vehicle, because no matter where you are, some people are just jerks!

Listing Title: The cottage guest house
Description:
Come and stay in our beautiful 1,100 sq. foot guest house located in the heart of Arlington, TX. We are  3/4 of a mile walk to the AT&T stadium and Globe Life Park is a block farther. Other attractions include Six Flags, Hurricane Harbor, and many more. We are surrounded by all kinds of restaurants & shops! We are only a few blocks to the University of Texas at Arlington.

The cottage is a separate home behind our residence. Parking is available by the entrance to The Cottage for easy access.

There is parking down a long driveway on the side of our house that leads to The Cottage.

We are available to answer any questions since we live on the property. We enjoy visiting with our guests but, at the same time, we respect their privacy. They can contact us anytime they have a question or need help with anything.

Approximately a (10-15 minute walk) to the west side of AT&T Stadium. Perfect for those attending Cowboy games or other events who don’t want to worry about parking.

We would like to know why you are coming to Arlington. Is it for sports, wedding, graduation, just hangin' out? If there is more than the six, we need to ok any additional people that might be visiting you while you are here. We are not a place for parties or large family gatherings. We are in a quite neighborhood and want to be considerate of our neighbors as well.

Listing Title: Quiet, Sweet and Smart Home, Close to AT&T Stadium
Description:
**30 day min stay required per City Code**
Welcome to our house in the heart of Arlington, TX! Right by UTA, AT&T stadium, Global Life Park, Six Flags, Epic Waters and Verizon Theater! Easy access to I-20, I-30, TX-360, and only 25-min drive to DFW airport.
Guests will enjoy our comfy beds, cozy living room, brand new full kitchen, laundry and more! Smart features, including 4K Android TV, smart doorbell/lock.

***30 day minimum stay required per city code. Thank you for your understanding!***

The house is renovated 2 years ago, with a cozy living room, full kitchen, comfy beds, laundry and more! 
The house's 3 bedrooms are furnished with 1 king size bed, 1 queen size bed and 1 twin-over-full bunk bed, respectively. Plus, there are 1 sofa bed, 1 queen size and 1 twin size air mattresses available for extra guests. 2 full bathrooms including 1 walk-in bath with tub in the master bedroom.
Kitchen is equipped with all major also small appliances. Cookware/flatware are ready for you to enjoy the your meals with family and friends. Board games are also available to have more fun, cause why not?
More importantly, house is equipped with safety features like smoke detector and outdoor video surveillance to ensure you a quiet and safe stay here. We also have fire extinguishers and first aid kit just in case of emergencies. 
And of course, how can we not consider our lovely kids? The big backyard is perfect for them to play around! A little swing for some extra fun. Patio sofa set and grill are also available for use. For infants, we provide a foldable pack 'n play crib you can use wherever you go, a baby bouncer, a high chair and a baby bath tub! Also provided are basic supplies just in case you need them. Still, we kindly ask parents to take care of the kids carefully, a memorable fun stay is all we want you to have.

Loads of smart features can also be found in the house, including 4K Android TV, smart doorbell/lock can also be found in the house. Guaranteed easy check-in

Listing Title: 3.8 miles to AT&T Stadium & Globe Life Park
Description:
Newly renovated duplex conveniently close to AT&T Stadium and Globe Life Park. This property has two living rooms perfect for families and entertaining, as well as three bedrooms. Fully furnished and decorated to give you everything you need for an enjoyable stay.

I believe in our high standards of cleanliness and hygiene for this house in hopes it would make your stay more pleasurable. We always replace our bedding covers (duvet) with clean ones for new clients, so there is no need for a flat sheet. Our pillow cases have two covers on them. The floors are vacuumed and steam mopped to ensure our guests will have a clean space.

As a response to the recent worldwide Covid-19 concerns, we want to let our guests know that our cleaners use Lysol All-Purpose Cleaner Spray, Lemon Breeze,(Kills Germs )spray or 70% isopropyl alcohol to clean all faucets, switches, toilet seats, toilet handles, door knobs, kitchen countertops, couches, dining tables, inside of the refrigerator and bathrooms for your protection. Please carry your personal hygiene protection during the trip to maintain healthy sanitation practices. Be sure to wash your hands often and we wish you a safe and pleasant stay!

We also provide our guests with a Reverse Osmosis Water Filtration System for clean drinking water. (So you don't need to buy bottle water) Our kitchen is fully equipped. We have a spacious laundry room with laundry detergent, fabric softener, new washer and dryer. Prior to your arrival, please text me so I can disarm the alarm system remotely. Walmart and Kroger are with 2-5 minutes away. The Town home is around 3.8 miles away from AT& T Stadium and Globe Life Park and   a wide variety of shops and restaurants are very close by.

Entire house

We are always a text or call away. Either of us would be happy to share information about the area, points of attraction, restaurant recommendations, etc. Both of us live about 15 minutes away so can be available if something arises.

New tile floor,

Listing Title: Arlington Cottage - Quaint, Detached & Private
Description:
Effective 2/1/20, The City Council of Arlington has banned the existence of short term rentals; which is anything less than a 30+ day stay.   PLEASE CONTACT ME WITH ANY QUESTIONS ABOUT BOOKING.   I 100% oppose this ruling that dictates what I can/can't do with our guest house that is located ON our property! 
This is a 2 bedroom (both with queen beds), 1 bath, detached, guesthouse.

It's perfect for privacy of 2 couples.  Our property is on 1+acres, in the middle of Arlington.  We are 3.5 miles to the AT&T, Cowboys, and Globe Life Park.  We are 30 minutes to Dallas or  Ft Worth.  The bedrooms are large, the kitchen is stocked with the basics for coffee, cooking or baking.  There is a washer and dryer in the cottage.  We provide everything you need to enjoy your stay.   If there is something that we forgot - a simple text to us, should resolve the issue.   The cottage has its own private back patio, parking and front porch chairs for relaxing. The cottage has wifi, two flat screen tv's, a full size fridge, washer/ dryer.  Both bedrooms have queen mattresses.

I have stocked our guesthouse with all the amenities. The kitchen has everything you need: Dishes, pans, glass wear, cooler, coffee, creamer, sugar, ziplocks.  The bathroom is stocked with towels, kleenex, shampoo, conditioner and soap.  There is a private patio for our guest house and there is parking for two cars. One space is covered.    We have two TV's:  One in the front living room and one in the back bedroom. We have Directv and Roku or ChromeCast.  There is also a DVD player in the living room TV.  We also offer dedicated wifi network for our guest.     
Lastly, there is  a washer and dryer inside the guest house.

Our main home is also located on the 1+ acre property, but the location of the cottage allows you complete privacy.

We are located in central Arlington on a old pecan orchard.  The neighborhood is gorgeous and ideal for relaxing or taking walks on tree lined streets.

Welcome to the Little Green Cottage - an original Sears Craftsmen’s House that’s newly remodeled, 2 bedroom 1 bath cottage in a quiet west Arlington neighborhood with a country charm to it.  It is minutes from AT&T stadium, Globe Life Park, TexasLive!, Six Flags, Hurricane Harbor and UTA to name a few. Very quite and safe neighborhood with a country feel to the place and surrounding properties.

Listing Title: Historic Arlington Home w/ Deck Near Attractions!
Description:
Originally constructed in 1913, 'The Lone Star House of Quilts' was once a popular quilt shop. Now, it's a lovely 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom vacation rental house in Arlington that's ideal for 10 travelers ready to experience everything Arlington has to offer! Attend sports games, dine at unique local restaurants, and peruse shops downtown before returning home at night to enjoy a glass of wine on the deck while taking in the views of the meticulously-manicured backyard.

Master Bedroom: King Bedroom | Bedroom 2 (Graham Room): King Bed | Bedroom 3 (Loft): 3 Queen Beds, Twin Bed 

Upon arrival, you'll be greeted by vibrant, green trees surrounding the home, including a 150-year-old magnolia tree inviting you right up to the lovely front porch. 

Inside, the home boasts 1,800 square feet of delicately appointed living space, featuring comfy furnishings, homey decor, and nice windows throughout, allowing the sun to illuminate every room. 

From the front living area with a stunning fireplace and the second living area with comfy couches and a TV to the spacious dining room and the fully equipped kitchen, this wonderful home has everything you need in a true home away from home. 

Just as the interior offers cozy spaces to sit back and relax, the exterior also features a whole other area to unwind on the spacious deck in the beautiful backyard! Waking up to sip a freshly-brewed cup of coffee on the darling front porch, you'll look forward to every morning at this wonderful abode. 

After a day of fun in the Lone Star State, everyone in your group will sleep comfortably in one of the plush beds. The home features 2 king beds, 3 queen beds, and a twin sized bed.

Evolve Vacation Rental makes it easy to find and book properties you'll never want to leave. You can relax knowing that our properties will always be ready for you and that we'll answer the phone 24/7. Even better, if anything is off about your stay, we'll make it right. 2 miles from AT&T Stadium, Globe Life Park, major theme parks Six Flags & Hurricane Harbor.

Everything except a closet that we keep locked for supplies.

Recently remodeled 3 bdrm 2 bath two miles south of AT&T Stadium, Globe Life Park, Six Flags & Texas LIVE! Conveniently located minutes from anywhere in the metroplex. Easy access to major highways. ******Bedroom #3 is a twin over double futon******

******PLEASE NOTE... SPECIAL EVENTS ARE AT A HIGHER RATE*******

You will be renting the whole house and have access to all areas with the exception of the garage.

We strive for your 5-Star Review and are happy to do what we can to make your stay pleasant. My wife and I are a short distance away and available 24/7 during your stay via call or text. In the event of emergencies there is a House Book with helpful information. Although it is preferred to meet all guests during check in, there are times when that isn't possible. Access for self check in through lockbox is available with prior arrangements with host.

Established neighborhood in east/central Arlington close to major highways. In the heart of the metroplex with easy access to I-30, I-20, 360 and the George Bush Tollway (161).

Listing Title: Arlington Apartment Near AT&T Stadium & Six Flags!
Description:
Set your sights on Arlington when staying at this 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom vacation rental apartment that sleeps up to 6 guests! Boasting a central location, this fully furnished home provides travelers with quick and easy access to all of the major destinations of this Texas city. Catch a Cowboy's game at the AT&T Stadium, seek thrills at Six Flags or Hurricane Harbor, and feast on mouthwatering local cuisine, all located within minutes of the property. Plan your Lone Star State getaway today!

Bedroom 1: Queen Bed | Bedroom 2: Queen Bed | Bedroom 3: Queen Bed 

Settle in for a relaxing Arlington retreat in this tastefully furnished, 1,000-square-foot apartment! Amenities including wireless internet access and in-unit laundry machines make you feel right at home - you can even keep up with your favorite shows on the flat-screen cable TV!

After a day of sightseeing, whip up mouthwatering feasts in the fully equipped kitchen! Modern appliances and ample countertops make home-cooking more than easy during your stay. Gather everyone around the 4-person dining table to savor your tasty creations. 

In the evenings, relax on the sumptuous leather furnishings with a nightcap or post-dinner coffee. Afterwards, enjoy a cleansing shower in one of the 2 full bathrooms, stocked with fresh towels. 

Thoroughly tired? Saunter off to one of the 3 bedrooms, furnished with cozy queen-sized beds, ceiling fans, and space to store your belongings. After a peaceful night's sleep, wake up feeling refreshed and ready for another day in Texas!

Evolve Vacation Rental makes it easy to find and book properties you'll never want to leave. You can relax knowing that our properties will always be ready for you and that we'll answer the phone 24/7. Even better, if anything is off about your stay, we'll make it right. You can count on our homes and our people to make you feel welcome--because we know what vacation means to you.

Listing Title: A Cozy Travel Trailer on Private EcoVillage Land
Description:
***30 nights minimum stay***

This trailer is uniquely situated within The Garden of Eden eco-village, a thriving small community dedicated to sustainability and philanthropy! 

With over 3 acres of land, herb and vegetable gardens, wildcrafted foods and medicine, and a handful of residents living here, the vibe is wholesome and progressive. 

Enjoy the privacy of the secluded trailer space, or join us on the grounds or in the main house for activities and communal meals by donation.

The trailer is cozy and private, though it is rustic and quite simple. As part of our ecovillage culture, we are dedicated to living sustainably and the trailer is set up with this in mind.  

Electricity does run to the trailer. It has a heater in winter and a small AC unit for the summer months.



There is a lock on the door for your privacy and comfort. We ask a $20 deposit for the key to the lock, which we will refund to you when you return it to us at the end of your stay.

The travel trailer is not hooked up to water. Wifi does not reach to the trailer in the back of our property, but you can come to the main house to connect.

We provide a complimentary continental breakfast for you with hot tea, seasonal fruits, a variety of organic milks & cereals, organic breads, and delicious spreads like jams and nut butters in our shared dining area of our main house.

You will have your choice of restroom facilities! We have a communal indoor bathroom in the main house with running water, flush toilets, and a hot shower available when our residents are awake (we generally have at least one person awake almost any time of day). 

We also have an outdoor shower that pumps 55 degree water straight from the Earth! It is crisp and refreshing on a hot day, and invigoratingly brisk in any other weather.  We invite you to try it if you wish! 

You also have access to your own private, outdoor, composting toilet just outside the trailer if you want to try the all natural route and donate your was

Listing Title: Whole house, 3 BR/3BA - Near ATT Stadium
Description:
This home is about 1.7 mile from ATT (Cowboys) Stadium and Globe Life (Ranger) Ballpark. The home is also close to Six Flags Hurricane Harbor (50-acre Water Park), Arlington Convention Center, and Restaurants, Bars, and Shopping. DFW and DAL airport are about 20 minutes away. Easy access to I-20, I-30, TX-360.

This home is completely renovated with open floor plan concept. Bedrooms are spacious and the Sun room provides separate sitting or play area for large group. 

The kitchen is equipped with pots and pans, knife, flatware, coffee maker for you to cook simple meals. There are three bedrooms, each bedroom has a queen bed, a desk+chair, a full-length mirror, so you can work, rest, and relax in your own room as well as in the common area.  Two single futon sofa are in living room and sunroom for additional sleepers.  Cloth dryer and washer with laundry detergent, fabric softener are located at the hall-way closet.  Hair dryer and iron/iron board are also available. Internet access is also available. 

All beds sheets, bath linens are replaced with clean ones after each guest stay. In particular, we always replace our comforter covers (duvet) with clean ones for new guests, so we don't provide a top flat sheet (similar practice to hotels in asia). Extra bed sheets and pillows are stored in bedroom's closet/chest-drawer for your need.

Everything except the car garage and a closet that we keep locked as storage.

We have self-check in system. We'll send a detailed info few days prior to your arrival. Please feel free to text us or call if you have any questions or something comes up during your stay, we're only a short drive away.

Prior to your arrival, please text Patty so we can be sure the house is ready for you.

This home is located in an established mature blue-collar neighborhood.  The neighborhood is close to all major entertainments in Arlington,  about 1.7 miles on map, (not walk-able to shops/stadium for most people).

Listing Title: House with a Private Bedroom
Description:
Nice cozy home in a great area in DFW near DFW Airport, At&t Stadium, Rangers stadium, UTA, TCC, Six Flags & Hurricane Harbor.

You will have your own private room with a Bed & Chair, which will also come with a key so you can lock the door to the room.

You will also have access to the livingroom as well as the kitchen and laudryroom area if you need to wash clothes.

You will be staying in a house with other people who occupy the other rooms in the house and they will also have access to the livingroom, kitchen & laundry room areas. Everyone is very courteous of others.

The neighborhood is a nice family neighborhood.

Stay in a lovely piece of Texas history. This 2 Bedroom home w/Jack and Jill bath retains its historic character and charm. Built in 1907, it is on the National Register of Historic Places. A perfect place for 1-5 people, 2 two blocks from downtown Arlington.  Great for work from home,a staycation, families. We offer weekly and monthly discounts. Due to the coronavirus we are following Airbnb guidelines for cleaning and disinfecting. We also leave the location empty for 4 days between stays.

Arlington Permit Number:
2019-139588-STR
A lovely historic home close to restaurants and night life, shuttles to events, free concerts on the lawn in the summer.  In between Dallas and Ft. Worth.
Close to Six Flags, Rangers Stadium, AT&T Stadium,Hurricane Harbor, University of Texas at Arlington, and The Arlington Music Hall. 8 miles from Lone Star Park live horse racing and Ripley’s Believe it or Not. 
If you need more space the adjacent Meg’s Loft is also available for rental.

6-8 miles away:

**Special Offers/Recognition Discounts - Please contact me if you qualify for any of the following special offers.  Discounts can only be applied by me and revised pricing offers will be sent privately, and directly to you.

-Military & First Responder Discount 10% - Active Duty, Retired, or Veteran.  Thank you for your service!

-Medical Travel 20% - For families traveling to receive specialized medical care/treatment from a local hospital, or those whose long distance family member is undergoing such.  Qualifying days to include recovery time if occupant is receiving care.

-Bereavement Travel 30% - Death of immediate family member of person booking: mother / father / siblings / grandparents / child / spouse

If you are requesting any of the discounts above please message me to discuss.  I will ask for verification before proceeding with your booking.
  - Military ID
  - Medical Pre-certification document for date(s) of treatment
  - Funeral service details (name of funeral home/dates) or death certificate, verifiable obituary identifying relation to person booking etc.

These can be a little tricky, and I understand the difficult time a family faces during the loss of a loved one or the stress that can come with a medical challenge.  Please understand I only ask for this to avoid false claimants to any discount.  I want to do all that I can to make your situation easier and provide a comfortable, worry-free stay for you & your family!

Listing Title: Comfort Zone
Description:
Spacious 4-bedroom house with the best-selected housemates. This house attracts companies housing their executive teams, to entrepreneurs, and working professionals. This house is a hidden gem with upgrades that allows you to escape in total luxury. Connect with other like-minded professionals. If by chance a room becomes available, we are looking to add you. Indeed, you are looking for the best space in Arlington, and that is what we are offering. Book now instantly to RSVP your spot today!

This house is perfect for professionals. If you are working in the area or you are relocating to the area, this house is excellent for networking and meeting other professionals on a similar path to you. This house is shared with a maximum of three additional guests in their individual private rooms. At most, the shower is shared, and the toilet is shared between the two guests upstairs. Rooms do book out fast and usually for an extended stay. The vibe is relaxed, chilled, and professional. If you can handle the vibe, you are most welcomed!

We take pride in keeping the space clean, which means everyone must do their part. You will be fully responsible for regularly maintaining and upkeeping cleaning in your private room. It is necessary to maintain cleaning standards throughout the house, especially in shared areas such as the kitchen. It is expected that dishes are washed daily, and additional sweeping and wiping down counters should be done as needed. Cleaning products and tools are available in the kitchen, bathroom, and home to use to clean. We like to maintain a neat, clean, and safe space for everyone to enjoy. Please reserve sleeping to your rooms and not on the sofa. Kindly remove shoes as you walk through the house.

Listing Title: Secured Parking ONLY for AT&T stadium events #1
Description:
This listing is for PARKING ONLY for any events at AT&T or Globe Life stadiums, not a room. I have SECURED parking. Unfortunately this listing no longer includes a ride to the stadium due to the COVID pandemic. It is a 7 minute walk to and from your vehicle from the AT&T stadium.

I will send you location details prior to your arrival. You will need to contact me via text when you're 10 minutes away. Once you arrive to the gate I will let you in, show you where to park your vehicle and show you how to get to the stadium; it's a straight shot to get there.

When you finish your activity and heading back to your car you will send me a text that you're heading my way. I will meet outside to let you in the gate so you can collect your vehicle.

Listing Title: The Bunk House on Elm
Description:
Located in the historic Old Town Neighborhood of Arlington,TX. This building was the first garage built by the first car owner in Arlington, but you would never guess it's origins! Walk to attractions, entertainment, eateries and breweries. With two bedrooms, large living area and cook friendly kitchen, this place is ideal. Eclectic and cozy setting for two or homey spot for friends and family traveling together.

The mattresses and bedding for all bedrooms are premium quality.   Anyone who has slept on a hide a bed knows that usually they are not great. But, our hide a bed in the living area has an upgraded adjustable air mattress.  All the guests who have slept on it agree that the comfort level is a huge surprise and enjoyed a great nights sleep. 

The kitchen has all the amenities you would expect to find in your own kitchen, with a Keurig coffee maker. We provide a few K-cups to get you started.

We are close to everything and more and more restaurants, bars and shops are being added all the time.  This is a very up and coming area!

Shared laundry room

I love to have the opportunity to greet my guests but realize that can’t always happen. We have a key pad entry so it is very convenient. I will always be available or someone will be on call for a assistance

We are so lucky to live in this neighborhood!  I love being so close to everything the Arlington has to offer. This area is in transition for the better and everyday something beautiful is happening.
I have started a vlog on Facebook that highlights the downtown area and the entertainment district. It’s still pretty new and I try not to be obnoxious with posts, but something is added each week.  Check out #downtowndarlin

We have a multitude of options for getting around. Walking is my favorite. Uber, Lyft, and a local ride share program called Via are available in this area

** Please Read**
Although we live in a wonderful and safe neighborhood I still take extra precautions to make sure our guest are safe and secure as possible. I have active video & audio surveillance around perimeter of home and front door entry. I can monitor activity in driveway and curbside where your car is parked and see who comes in and out of front door. Each guest will have their own separate temporary passcode to enter the premises.  I secured bedroom doors with doorlocks and provide guest with 2 keys so you can feel safe and keep your personal items secured.  I do not remake keys if guest loses a key, I install a new doorlock assembly and provide guest with a brand new key and spare.  I  placed video surveillance in hallways to prevent other guest from attempting to enter into your bedroom and prevent theft. I DO NOT place surveillance in bedrooms and bathrooms so please lock your door if you are not inside.  If you notice any suspicious activity or have personal items missing then please file a police report immediately. I will work with authorities to help resolve any issues and provide all video recordings if requested.

Please 'know' your guest you bring into the home and into the bedroom. When items come up missing it's usually from guest not really knowing their company.

Guests have access to the entire place, including private swimming pool,  private Tennis/Basketball court, to themselves. One spot of the garage is available. The other spot has a vehicle that will remain but not be accessed during your stay. One spot in the garage is used to store our antique car.

We may stop by to do work on outside of house. There is a weekly yard service and pool service as well. We will not disturb you inside the house during your stay.

You and your guests will love taking a walk through this beautiful neighborhood with mature trees. There is a very nice large park just down the road to take a walk or hike through the trails.

Lyft and Uber are very easy to grab for transportation and a great option to avoid crazy parking fees at the stadium.

There is a shed on the property that is not included in the rental.

The following services are mandatory to ensure the property is taken care of during your stay:

Pool service comes once a week. We also check on the pool a couple times a week in between services to remove leaves.

Yard service comes every other week.

Listing Title: The Library
Description:
1 bedroom, loft, and bath. Purple mattress in the master bedroom. Full kitchen with all of the essentials for some home cooking. The parks mall(5 miles), Arlington Highlands(6 miles), ATT Stadium(10 miles), and Six Flags(12 miles) are all minutes away. Fiber optic internet and Amazon Fire TV with Netflix for entertainment. I have a lot of books. Pick one up, learn something new. 
Message me now to "book" your stay. 
===========
Due to local laws all stays must be a minimum of 30 nights.

The house is on my grandparents land. It is the guest house behind their house. We live on two and a half acres. Self check in. Sleeping arrangements upstairs are a trundle bed with two twin mattresses and an optional air mattress that can be setup.(Please let me know  if you will be needing the air mattress).

The entire place is all yours!

Traffic can be bad at times on the major highways and around the stadiums during events. I would allot a minimum of 20 minutes for every 10 miles traveled.

I have a 2021 Tesla model 3 available for rent on Turo. If you are in need of a car for your stay I can give you the details after your reservation is made as Airbnb does not allow links here.

Listing Title: ★Exclusive 1+ Acre Wooded Retreat by AT&T Stadium★
Description:
If you are looking for a UNIQUE HOUSE nestled next to an ACRE OF DENSELY WOODED FOREST to relax at - YOU'VE FOUND IT!  You can see the stadiums from our yard.

Just a SHORT WALK to Cowboys Stadium. Save parking fees! Fast drive to Six Flags, Rangers, The Cowboys and Texas Live!

Granite kitchen and custom fixtures. TV's & Wooded View in every bedroom! One Xbox 360 is centrally located and can be played wirelessly to any bedroom or TV. Please read entire listing!

Arlington Permit 2019-124091-STR

** MAX OCCUPANCY AT ANY TIME - INCLUDING DAYTIME IS 8 PERSONS ** Please contact me if you have questions concerning this before booking. 

This is our quiet, cul-de-sac vacation house in the city, and we’d love to share this location that has easy I-30 access to Dallas and Ft. Worth! If you want to be in the middle of all the entertainment, but feel like you are in the country. This is as close as it gets in this area!!

Brand new renovation, cozy carpet in bedrooms, and the only house left offering a huge wooded acre lot, right in the city. Most of your basic necessities are here for you - shampoo, soaps, laundry detergent, hangers and an ironing board. USB charging ports by every bed.

In the kitchen you'll have a coffee pot with coffee and supplies, blender, bottle/can openers, a few pots and pans, plates, cups, and utensils. Sometimes we will stock the fridge with extra goodies. Don't worry, there is a dishwasher - no hand washing needed!

We also have a custom computer desk, made out of old reclaimed barn wood, built under a window with forest view. If you don't have a laptop with you - feel free to use our vintage manual typewriter ;)

NEARBY ATTRACTIONS
Located in Central Arlington, you'll find it an easy drive (or Uber) to many popular destinations.

Cowboys Stadium - 20 min walk!
Many Restaurants & Bars - 10-15 min walk!
Texas Live! - 1.5 Miles
Arlington Convention Center -  1.7 Miles
Esports Stadium -  1.7 Miles

Hurricane Harbor - 1.8 Miles

Listing Title: South Arlington Home with Large Upstairs Space
Description:
Fully renovated modern Farmhouse .  Warm and friendly home in DFW area.  Close to 287 and I-20 with easy access to Dallas and Fort Worth.  Easy access to Six FLags, Cowboy Stadium, Ranger Ballpark, TCU and UTA with several malls near and lots of entertainment.   Great space for groups coming in for sports events,  great  accomadations for families with small children and great space for businessmen and women.

This listing is for the upstairs  two large bedrooms and common space.  Additional guests over 2 is an additional 10.00 a person per night.  While there is not a private entrance for this space, the upstairs does close off from the downstairs and has a private feel. The upstairs inludes two oversized bedrooms, a living space, full bath and a sink area off one of the bedrooms.  Total bed count is: 2 queen beds.  We have more bedding options so please inquire with your needs.  Space includes a coffee maker, mini fridge and a microwave. $95 per night for 4.

Guest will have access to a swimming pool and outdoor play ground with prior approval.  The property sits on 2 acres of land and has  a chicken coop on the property.

We will be available either on the spot or by text or phone.  The owners may be present on the property but are welcoming and friendly.  There are two dogs that live in the home but have never been upstairs.  We have two additional bedrooms downstairs with a queen bed in one room and a room with a full bed.  Please message if you are in need of additional space.

This home sits on 2 acres with homes around us but not in a "neighborhood" which provides for quiet and country feel.

We have two nearby parks in walking distance or a quick drive.  We are near 287 and I-20 with easy access to I-35 and 360.

We love to share our home !

Listing Title: Chic and Comfy 2 Story Home for Big Groups
Description:
*******THIS LISTING ONLY ALLOWS STAYS OF 30+ DAYS***** 
An exciting group trip needs to be balanced with private space. You want to create unforgettable memories, but don’t want to step on each other’s toes. This recently renovated two story home in Arlington, TX is perfectly equipped for both.

This fantastic house is fully equipped with every possible luxury you could ever desire: we've got you covered from head to toe with the most lavish, plushest, softest, best smelling and most exquisite amenities possible.

Our home is a hop, skip and a jump from everything wonderful, exciting and vibrant that DFW has to offer.  Located in a quiet neighborhood in Arlington TX, we are 5 minutes from AT&T Stadium and Six Flags, 15-20 minutes from DFW Airport, 20-25 minutes from both downtown Dallas and downtown Fort Worth.

Every room in the house makes you feel comfortable and stylish. The decor is European Chic and plays around with different colors and fabrics. Vibrant colors improve your mood, eye-catching paintings and statues add an extra level of style.

An enormous living room is perfect for movies, games, or drinks. The dining room is gorgeously furnished and fits twelve people. 

The kitchen features new appliances. It’s big enough to make cooking fun, let everyone help out, and NEVER have too many cooks in the kitchen. No matter how hungry you all are, the dining room is big enough to eat in. Fourteen chairs allow for a proper feast.

Each bedroom features a different sleeping arrangement. So no matter if your trip filled with bachelors and bachelorettes, couples, or a family, you are well equipped. The master bedroom has a king size bed, 42" smart TV and a full en-suite bathroom. The second bedroom has a queen and a bunk bed -- perfect for a whole family. The third bedroom has two bunk beds. The fourth bedroom has a queen bed and a bunk bed. The fifth also has two bunk beds (please note, the 5th bedroom will only be available for groups of 12+ people).

Built in 1942, this home has been remodeled but holds the charm and nostalgia with the original doors and hardwood floors. It is literally across the street from Cowboys stadium!In the heart of the Entertainment District.Walk to local happenings like AT&T & Rangers Stadiums,Texas Live!Downtown Arlington is alive with new restaurants, breweries and night life!!

Just so you are prepared, this home is prone to the noise of the stadium, so if you are a light sleeper, bring your earplugs..unless you plan to be part of it all!!

I enjoy meeting all my guests at check in if possible.  I am usually very close as I own the two homes next door.  Outside perimeter cameras are mock cameras and have no recording capabilities.  If you need me after 10:00 pm please give a voice phone call.  Otherwise text is best.
